blog.title: Try, try, try again.
blog.description: My weight loss journey to a healthier, happier life. *Vegetarian -- Start: July 2017 125.1kg // 276lbs CW: 107.1kg // 237lbs.

title: An update on my challenge...
body:
Remember when I said:

- no ice cream
- no bread
- no pop/soda
- no alcohol
- no chips/french fries
- no pizza/junk food

Fasting 8pm to 12pm (midday).

Well, 12 days in and the only thing I’ve broken is the bread rule - which I don’t think is as important as the other points. The fasting is easy to be honest. It’s quite interesting to reflect so far because the cravings are going and when I do think of these foods, I quickly tell myself that I don’t eat them and I let them go. I’ve lost quite a bit of weight already but I’ll update you on Thursday - the two week weigh in. Next week I have a school event so I was going to take a day off from this, but now I’m thinking that I’ll just take my own food and stick with being healthy.

summary: He slept at my place and late at night started sneezing and coughing. I mixed him my favorite flu killer made of grinded ginger,...
body: He slept at my place and late at night started sneezing and coughing. I mixed him my favorite flu killer made of grinded ginger, honey and turmeric. This mixture has helped me avoid a full blown cold many times. When the first signs show up I instantly take a good amount of the flu killer and it works its magic. He woke up feeling refreshed and energized, no more sneezing and coughing. “It’s almost like you’re a witch.” One of the best compliments I got so far.

title: The heart - a striking marvel
body:
The heart beats about three billion times in the course of a human life. An awesome achievement!

Miracle of nature

The heart is a marvel of nature: The fist-shaped hollow muscle contracts about seventy times a minute, pumping up to 10,000 liters a day through the body. And for a lifetime. If necessary - when jogging about - the heart even transports five times as much blood through the body.

Double work

Actually, our heart is made up of two pumps. Because there is not just one bloodstream, but two. The right ventricle pumps blood into the lungs, where it replenishes with oxygen. At the same time, the left ventricle conveys the same amount of blood into the systemic circulation. Not easy. Because in the systemic circulation there is much higher pressure than in the pulmonary circulation.

Boom, boom

Each half of the heart consists of an atrium and a ventricle. The blood can only flow in one direction, because there are heart valves (green) between the atria and the chambers and between the chambers and the subsequent vessels, which work like check valves.

Real muscle work

The heart is just a muscle - but a very special one. He is similar to those on the arm and leg, because he can contract just as fast and powerful. But he is very persistent and does not tire. In addition, all myocardial cells are coupled to each other so that the entire heart muscle always contracts at the same time.

Natural pacemaker

Try to prevent your heart from beating by willpower! This does not work, because the heart is not controlled by nerves, but has its own clock: Special muscle cells in the sinus node regularly generate a small current surge, which spreads as lightning throughout the heart and makes it contract. If the sinus node is defective, the AV node takes over.

Out of rhythm

If the heart gets out of rhythm, for example, in the case of ventricular fibrillation, it no longer relaxes, but remains constantly cramped. Then the organ can no longer pump blood. A shock generator, the defibrillator, interrupts the life-threatening constant agitation in the heart so that the natural clock can take over again. Even a layman can operate the device.

Rescuer

If a patient’s heart beats too slowly, an artificial pacemaker will help. The device generates electrical impulses and forwards them to the heart muscle. For the first time, physicians implanted a pacemaker in 1958. A modern pacemaker has a functional life of between five and twelve years, an average of eight years.

At the open heart

In order to operate on the heart, the doctors have to stop it for a short time and shut down the circulation - actually a death sentence. But in the 1950s scientists solved the dilemma: They developed the heart-lung machine. The device takes over the function of the heart and lungs for a short time, enriches the blood with oxygen and pumps it through the body.

Through the bar into the heart

Modern medicine makes it possible to examine the heart or to operate it without cutting the patient’s ribcage. For this purpose, the doctor introduces a cardiac catheter - a thin plastic tube, as it were - through the groin, the elbow or the wrist and pushes the tube over the veins or arteries to the heart. The patient is previously only locally anesthetized.

Foldable heart valve

If one of the heart valves is broken or worn out, a new one must be produced. Doctors resort to either biological replacement of the pig or mechanical metal heart valves. Meanwhile, there are also artificial heart valves, which are collapsible (see photo) and can therefore be used minimally invasive via a catheter. An open heart surgery is then no longer necessary.

Clogged vessels

The coronary arteries supply the heart muscle with blood, ie nutrients and oxygen. Clogged one of these vessels, the no longer perfused tissue dies - heart attack! With a bypass, the cardiac surgeon bridges the narrowed area (green in the picture). For this he takes a vein of the patient, which is no longer needed, or a plastic vascular prosthesis.

Lifesaver made of metal

If a coronary vessel is narrowed, the doctor can insert a catheter into the blood vessel and dilate the constriction with a balloon. In order to prevent the vessel from contracting afterwards, it is held open with a stent: these are fine metal sleeves that support the blood vessel wall from the inside. The tubes may also be coated with drugs.

When your own heart no longer wants

The first heart transplant was performed by cardiac surgeons in 1967. At that time a sensation. In the meantime, surgery is no longer a rarity: every year doctors transplant thousands of donor hearts from deceased people worldwide. However, the recipients must take a lifetime of drugs that prevent your own body rejects the foreign organ.

Life on Pump

Donor hearts are rare. If your own heart is no longer functioning properly, such as in case of insufficiency, it can be supported with an artificial heart. The own, diseased heart remains in the body, it is supported by an implanted pump. Drive and power supply of the pump are outside the body.

An artificial heart


The Explorer’s dream is an artificial heart that completely replaces the patient’s diseased heart. It should be able to be used without connecting hoses to the outside world in the body and beat maintenance-free many years. Prototypes already exist.

summary: hope I can deal with life.
body:
back to basics

Now I am drying my hair and thinking of what is really important. Always a tough thought.

As my life have been changing I am about to make it properly.

So my mission is to stop being a piece of trash.

Sounds easy and fucking hard at the same time, right?

It is the beginning of my 10th week of being sober. No more alcohol in my life, ‘cause I’m fed up with it.

I’ll start with the stuff I’ve already did:

  • #soberlife
  • working hard analyzing all my past
  • severe work on my flaws, issues and insecurities (but still in process, can’t be sure when it’s time so stop)
  • developing skills in being close with people, 'cause one day it came up that mine are bad as hell
  • collecting knowledge on defferent spheres of life-i-want-to-have

The next level is:

  • to continue work with my personality and mind
  • to pay attention to my physical health:
  1. healthy nutrition, first of all. cpfc (calories, protein, fat, carbohydrates in right proportions), more veggies and fruits. fats from nuts, fish, avocado, oils, seeds. lean protein + protein supplies. minimize fast carbohydrates. no more than 24g of added sugar. cool breakfasts. 5+ portions of food/day. no calorie-packed stuff for dinner. sea products 3 times/week. cheat meals on weekends.
  2. fitness (strength + cardio)
  3. water balance
  4. good sleep
  5. massage, creams, oils, scrubs 😜
  6. vitamins and minerals
  • stop smoking
  • start reading fiction literature
  • more more more education
  • language practice + second foreign language
  • c++
  • continue drawing and other hobbies
  • start again morning and evening routines

So let’s take this for the first time. Every week I will write about my progress or failure.

hope I can deal with life.

blog.title: Mens Bodybuilding Tips
blog.description: Physical Therapist and Fitness Consultant. I bring you some Amazing Bodybuilding exercises along with high protein tips and workouts for health and weight loss

summary: Arnold Schwarzenegger: Rears in High Gear
title: Arnold Schwarzenegger: Rears in High Gear
body:
A lot of people treat their rear deltoids as a second thought. After all, compared to many other, much larger muscles (especially chest, back and quads), the back delts are fairly small. Over the years, I have actually seen rear delt training totally ignored, and I’ve likewise observed several individuals hitting this section of their shoulder musculature ineffectively.

It could be challenging and also awkward to isolate the rear delts. Pressing activities rely much more on the front as well as middle delts, while bent-over side elevates require extreme emphasis so momentum or your back muscular tissues don’t take over. Another secret is not utilizing also much weight– the back delts are so little that you have to keep the resistance light or your body will certainly involve various other, larger muscles to assist perform the lift. 

You could train your rear delts with dumbbells, cables or equipments, and I believe you ought to utilize each of these pieces of equipment. That said, below are 3 of my preferred back delt isolation exercises.

BENT-OVER DUMBBELL LATERAL RAISE 

To target the back delts with dumbbells, start the lift bent over with your upper body extremely close to alongside the floor. I always liked to do this sitting on the end of a bench, former Mr. Olympia Lee Haney did this move flexing over while standing up. Either way is great as long as you’re able to separate the tension on the rear delts.

Train to obtain big! See exactly what Steve Kuclo provides for dimension as well as strength.

CABLE BENT-OVER LATERAL RAISE 

This is simply the cable version of the previous exercise, it was always one of my preferred back delt moves because of the constant stress cable televisions provide. Stand between two lowpulley cables, grasping the opposite takes care of so the wires cross in front of you. Bend over up until your torso is almost identical to the flooring and lift the manages bent on your sides, elbows curved somewhat, starting with your palms dealing with in as well as pronating your wrists during the activity to further isolate the back delts.

REVERSE PEC-DECK FLYE

There are rear delt devices in numerous health clubs, and some pec decks could be used to hit the rear delts if you sit facing the machine as opposed to putting your back against the pad. As soon as you have actually discovered to train the rear deltoids with pinheads and cables, you should know what it seems like to strike these muscle mass in isolation. Just see to it you obtain that same feeling when making use of an equipment. - FLEX

Another secret is not utilizing also much weight– the back delts are so little that you have to keep the resistance light or your body will certainly involve various other, larger muscles to assist perform the lift. 

You could train your rear delts with dumbbells, cables or equipments, and I believe you ought to utilize each of these pieces of equipment. That said, below are 3 of my preferred back delt isolation exercises.

BENT-OVER DUMBBELL LATERAL RAISE 

To target the back delts with dumbbells, start the lift bent over with your upper body extremely close to alongside the floor. I always liked to do this sitting on the end of a bench, former Mr. Olympia Lee Haney did this move flexing over while standing up. Either way is great as long as you’re able to separate the tension on the rear delts.

Train to obtain big! See exactly what Steve Kuclo provides for dimension as well as strength.

CABLE BENT-OVER LATERAL RAISE 

This is simply the cable version of the previous exercise, it was always one of my preferred back delt moves because of the constant stress cable televisions provide. Stand between two lowpulley cables, grasping the opposite takes care of so the wires cross in front of you. Bend over up until your torso is almost identical to the flooring and lift the manages bent on your sides, elbows curved somewhat, starting with your palms dealing with in as well as pronating your wrists during the activity to further isolate the back delts.

REVERSE PEC-DECK FLYE

There are rear delt devices in numerous health clubs, and some pec decks could be used to hit the rear delts if you sit facing the machine as opposed to putting your back against the pad. As soon as you have actually discovered to train the rear deltoids with pinheads and cables, you should know what it seems like to strike these muscle mass in isolation. Just see to it you obtain that same feeling when making use of an equipment. - FLEX
